Notes:
after indian holidays & peus de moix. The bottom 3 bolts is unbelievable climbing!!! - then ok climbing to another nice boulder problem off a jug near top then easy exit.

Start 
- r hand jug pocket, left hand slot.
- L hand up to DEEP 2f pocket, r foot up, r hand pocket. L cross to deep pocket.
- R foot into hueco like hole, right hand cross to pocket. L Hand come through to better L pocket
- up with left to deep undercling pocket. L Foot up to big hueco out left, r hand ou to slopey crimp, bump to jug. 
- bring L foot into closest pocket, L Hand up. 

Off jug
- L hand deep incut slot above jug
- R hand up to 3 finger crimp
- L Hand out to hole, pinch it! Sink body underneath.
- Right hand crimp
- L Hand to DEEP pocket just left of draw.

The start is 6/5 stars. Overall 4/5 stars.
Location: International > Europe > Spain > Catalonia > Margalef > Can dit Gros

Notes:
falls - still jet-lagged & exhausted from the travel. Had fun on this great climb though! 4/5 stars. Awesome, but not quite demon seed/ghostrider/orange juice level though.

At bulge: Left hand jug, right hand to first sidepull that is quite good! Left foot comes through and flag - lots of black rubber, v-slot shape. Left hand up to ok crimp, bump to left Jug slot. - not hard, just a lot of options :)

Crux - the money beta: Left hand good hold, right hand epic jug sidepull. Right foot up to small edge, left foot up to good foot, right foot up high to BLACK foot. Get that foot set! Hips in tight, right hand to small crimp, bump right hand again to great jug!

Excellent beta from Liane!

Only other thing to note: Above the crux, before the next draw, use the small left sidepull crimp to get feet up and established, to make reach for ticked jug.

Notes:
This is an amazing climb!

Boulder, easy but fun climbing, crux boulder at bolt 7 (described below), one more crux after amazing horizontal shake. Going to anchors looks intimidating but the crimps on the slab are positive

Just too smoked today. 

First boulder: use the small, pebbly crimp for the right hand + a high left foot to reach the left hand sidepull. Not hard this way at all :) the pocket out to the right is not any good - slopey and in a bad position

At crux - where there’s tons of chalk - get two hands on crimps, high right foot with right hip in directly underneath two crimps, make a big lunge to a great hold. 

KEY: Get on, in either frigid temps OR while top is still in the shade for the crux. (Goes into sun around noon in late October)

Notes:
With Joe. 2.5 star p1, 4 star stretch right before, through two cruxes and immediately following cruxes. 

Led p1 (200 feet), Joe led 10a section and built belay on small ledge, I led 10c crux with close belay and went all the way to the top.

BEST and safest way to do it for sure, that way you aren’t doing the crux of the route over a ledge with a 100 feet of rope out. All pitch lengths remain the same 

Notes for next time:
1. On p1, when you get near end, there is a scary looking part. You get micro cams in a flaring crack and it looks like you have to pull this sloper overlap with bad feet - you don’t, there’s a huge jug rail to the left.
2. On last part, there’s a scary looking move above the piton. There’s a really flaring pin scar and an insecure move on slopers. A bd z4 .5 fits this pin scar unbelievable well and is good enough to hold a leader fall. Make sure to have one!

Notes:
Absolutely Incredible! 1 fall (getting over roof) 1 take (2nd to last bolt). Take a left kneepad. Kneebar at huge undercling before stem rest. Can kneebar on tufa with hands in hole out of roof. Likely best to keep going

Skip 2nd to last bolt. There’s a draw at your knee

At roof, there is a big left foot to stem on when on tufa. Ticked mega jug pocket (black rock) just up and left of tufa. Can get huge rest here. Then at second to last draw (skip it), Right hand gaston, left hand undercling pocket, left foot mega foot. Right foot up onto ticked crimp, right hand cross through to jug.

Clip last bolt. Right hand sidepull, left hand sidepull (high) right foot on small black tick, left into pocket immediately under left hand. Stand, right hand into massive jug :)

Notes:
1 fall. Sorted the beta!!!!!!!! It’s a little complex: 

Left hand crimp, right hand middle crimp. Right foot big slopey knob, left foot middle smear

Left hand out to sidepull jug (hit it low middle, at the tick), right foot up to highest small knob. Right hand come in to left most crimp. 

Right foot COME BACK to big slopey knob, KEY: left foot out to farthest left smear, there is UNBELIEVABLE texture. Right hand match sidepull above right hand.

NOW, you’ve almost sent: left hand, left to slopey crimp, KEY right foot to middle smear, left foot KICK out to AMAZING foot left, left hand to crimp 

#1 pitch of the year
Location: Washington > Central-West Cascades & Seattle > Skykomish Valley > Index > The Country Area > (c) The Country

Notes:
Clean! No falls. Only 10 minutes after lead attempt. Epic pitch, I hope I get to lead it again

Crux: left hand on sloper nothing, right hand Gaston,  left foot out to GOOD foot (low), high right foot just right of seam, right hand to a 2 finger crimp pocket (looks like the seam) left foot up high on sloping chip. YOU HAVE to release the right foot and stand on the left foot, left hand into crack in the seam. Right foot high onto amazing small knob!

Crux is now over, right hand to flake, left hand to sidepull left of bolt (it’s a secret jug) clip!

THEN: right hand up to crimp, left in sidepull jug, high left foot: go BIG to jug. Right hand, hand jam the jug slot and go out left! 

After the last bolt, you have to move over to the adjacent route to do the finish move. The finish broke on the 12b

I’m going to scream. Sent the 12a again, fell on the fucking arete again.

Here is the fool-proof beta (new hold). Your feet HAVE to be EXACTLY right or it will not work.

Left hand sidepull thing, right hand arete. Left foot step through, right foot to chip on arete (RIGHT FOOT HAS to be on this chip on the arete. It does not work if it’s on edge directly below body) left foot on edge, grab left sidepull. 

Then it’s OVER

Notes:
1 fall on onsight go. Sent through the first crux, but fell on the bulge first go. Went next time with very powerful Gaston move

Crux 1: left foot needs to end on edge just below huge rail. Right foot on black rubber big foot. Left thumb press, right crimp. Left up to 3 finger positive crimp, right up to left Gaston crimp, big move to sidepull jug. 

Crux 2: get massive rail just over bulge (it is huge) left hand Gaston. right foot high onto big foot, pull hips in really tight. Must keep core tight! Big move to jug with right hand (do not get suckered into underclings! Hold right next to bolt is very big)

Really really well protected/bolted climb

Notes:
Led every pitch with Jordan following

Onsight 2, 6.
Redpoint 1, 5
Fell/hung 3,4,7

P1: fingercrack is less than vertical. Lock and smear and you’re by a wide margin strong enough to get to the hand jam/stem rest at top of fingers

Incinerator: STAY TIGHT! climb fast and find finger locks to place. Cannot sow it up. Pull hips into wall to place. Would a right leg Drop knee work?? Climbing is easy, placing is strenuous. Good hand jams and a .75 near top of crack

Boulder problem: right hand undercling, right foot jam, left hand palm press, left foot edge -> left foot onto arete, trust it, right foot onto sloper below undercling, right hand Gaston undercling, stand up to jug

Pitch 5: hidden jug at most awkward part, right before thin hands/overhang (in the hole, can’t see before committing)

Pitch 7: crank on thin hands (don’t try to ring lock), get feet up, tight hand jam
Location: California > Yosemite National Park > Yosemite Valley > Valley South Side > Q. Leaning Tower Area > Fifi Buttress
